main event: Observation of three unidentified objects in Portland, Oregon on March 6, 1961.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 9 minutes, The objects were described as larger and much brighter than stars, The objects were related out of sight at about 45-50 degrees above the southeast horizon, The sighting was corroborated by two other individuals within 10 minutes of each other, The objects were later identified as Echo 1 through Space Track.
witness description: One was a 25-year-old foundry worker and another was a 15-year-old student.
